{
  "texts": [
    "By Lemma 2.8, ϵ(AE b (X)) therefore consists of those functionals on Lip c (X) = Lip b (X) which are linear and continuous with respect to pointwise convergence with bounded Lipschitz constants.",
    "By definition, this is the space D 0 (X).Corollary 2.10.",
    "For any x ∈ X, the evaluation functionalπ → π(x) on Lip b (X) is a measure in the sense that π → π(x) = π dδ x for every π ∈ Lip(X),where δ x is the Dirac measure at x.",
    "If X is compact, then for every metric 0-current T on X, there exists a sequence of measures µ i on X such thatsup π∈Lip b,1 (X) | π dµ i -T (π)| → 0.Proof.",
    "The first statement is trivial."
  ]
}